Cookies
This website uses “cookies” to distinguish you from other users. A cookie is a small file placed on your computer or device. This helps us to provide you with a good experience when you browse our website and also allows us to improve our site and services. The cookies are stored locally on your computer or mobile device. To accept cookies close this window and continue browsing as normal. Or you can go to our cookie policy to read more information and learn how to change your preferences.
What if I change my mind about your use of cookies?
Our Site sometimes uses cookies to track how our visitors move through the Site. We use this information to identify areas of the Site that are of interest to investors or that can be improved.
The cookies we use don’t include any information about your personal identity or your accounts. Simply accepting cookies from our Site does not compromise the security of your accounts. We don’t display account information on this Site.
Most web browsers are set up to automatically accept cookies. Users can, however, amend the configuration of the web browser on their computers so that they are systematically notified of any instance where the Websites that they are about to visit contain cookies.
